            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="1142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/1–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-19T17:00:00-05:00">January 19, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Embtel 95 Jan 12 rptd Paris 3 London 2. Having in mind current situation
                        Tientsin<note n="8" xml:id="d1142fn8">Tientsin was occupied by the Chinese
                        Communists on January 15; for documentation regarding problems of the
                        Consulate General at Tientsin after the occupation, see <ref target="#pg_1051">pp. 1051</ref> ff.</note> and unwillingness British
                    and French join in press statement Dept believes issuance press statement re
                    denial communication facilities ConGen Mukden unwise at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
